1
00:00:02,923 --> 00:00:06,590
Strong foundation is necessary.

2
00:00:08,130 --> 00:00:15,287
So that what is built
upon the foundation will last,

3
00:00:15,287 --> 00:00:18,460
be something 
lasting and substantial.

4
00:00:18,818 --> 00:00:22,057
[Modest Natural Growth]

5
00:00:22,530 --> 00:00:25,450
I’ve told
when I saw the gate

6
00:00:25,450 --> 00:00:28,300
under construction 
at Govinda Kuṇḍa,

7
00:00:28,300 --> 00:00:31,755
and saw they’re digging
so deep into the ground,

8
00:00:31,755 --> 00:00:34,448
I asked Śrīla Āchārya Mahārāj,

9
00:00:34,448 --> 00:00:36,853
“Why are they digging so deep?”

10
00:00:36,853 --> 00:00:40,763
He said, “So, it’ll have
a strong foundation.”

11
00:00:40,763 --> 00:00:46,243
And then the gate 
will last forever.

12
00:00:46,243 --> 00:00:56,157
So, there is a tendency
for new recruits or neophyte devotees

13
00:00:56,157 --> 00:01:01,536
to try to go too far, 
too soon, too fast.

14
00:01:04,641 --> 00:01:10,281
We’ve seen the mangoes 
on the trees outside the studio.

15
00:01:10,681 --> 00:01:15,861
And it’s so tempting 
to pick one.

16
00:01:16,722 --> 00:01:20,793
But a month goes by,
another month goes by,

17
00:01:20,793 --> 00:01:22,424
another month goes by,

18
00:01:22,424 --> 00:01:26,814
and they’re just approaching 
the ripe stage.

19
00:01:27,099 --> 00:01:35,149
But it’s so tempting to pull it,
pluck it prematurely.

20
00:01:35,152 --> 00:01:42,062
That’s the conundrum,

21
00:01:42,642 --> 00:01:50,012
one of the difficulties 
experienced by the neophyte,

22
00:01:50,302 --> 00:01:54,139
whereas Guru Mahārāj 
advises us,

23
00:01:54,268 --> 00:01:57,260
‘modest natural growth’.

24
00:01:57,260 --> 00:01:59,490
They do this thing in India,

25
00:01:59,500 --> 00:02:06,720
they artificially 
ripen mangoes with carbide,

26
00:02:08,009 --> 00:02:12,139
because people 
are so eager for the mangoes.

27
00:02:12,139 --> 00:02:17,693
They can’t wait for them
to come to market at the natural time.

28
00:02:17,719 --> 00:02:26,447
So, they put this artificial,
this horrible chemical in them somehow,

29
00:02:26,447 --> 00:02:30,087
and it artificially ripens them.

30
00:02:30,927 --> 00:02:34,699
And if you’ve ever had one,
it tastes horrible actually.

31
00:02:34,699 --> 00:02:39,067
If you get one by mistake
you’ll know.

32
00:02:40,029 --> 00:02:41,879
So …

33
00:02:45,039 --> 00:02:48,499
Modest natural growth.

34
00:02:49,650 --> 00:02:52,020
Sometimes Guru Mahārāj 
would quote this thing,

35
00:02:52,020 --> 00:02:56,730
“Deserve, then desire”,

36
00:02:57,026 --> 00:02:59,276
or Śrīla Prabhupād’s
famous statement:

37
00:02:59,276 --> 00:03:01,723
“Work now—samādhi later!”

38
00:03:01,723 --> 00:03:04,833
[Laughing]

39
00:03:04,833 --> 00:03:06,813
Saraswatī Ṭhākur, 
Guru Mahārāj said, 
 

40
00:03:06,813 --> 00:03:09,163
he would say 
to this one devotee,

41
00:03:09,163 --> 00:03:12,793
“I’ve got my eye on you.
I am aware

42
00:03:12,793 --> 00:03:15,903
of everything you’re doing, 
all the sevā you’re doing.

43
00:03:15,903 --> 00:03:18,037
And the time will come
in the future,

44
00:03:18,037 --> 00:03:19,897
when you’re older”, 
he said,

45
00:03:19,897 --> 00:03:21,947
“I’ll give you one assistant,

46
00:03:21,947 --> 00:03:24,727
you’ll be taking Kṛṣṇa-nām
going deeper,

47
00:03:24,727 --> 00:03:27,927
but now continue as you are.

48
00:03:27,927 --> 00:03:33,947
But don’t think I am not seeing you,
unaware of what your position is.”

49
00:03:33,958 --> 00:03:37,258
That sort of faith 
we have to have also.

50
00:03:37,258 --> 00:03:41,678
śraddhānvito ’nuśṛṇuyād atha varṇayed yaḥ
[SB: 10.33.39]

51
00:03:41,678 --> 00:03:46,888
That as Guru Mahārāj would say,
“Our guardians are real!”

52
00:03:46,888 --> 00:03:50,841
Under the ever-watchful
eye of Yoga-māyā.

53
00:03:50,841 --> 00:03:53,747
She knows who needs what,

54
00:03:53,759 --> 00:03:58,428
which servitors need 
any particular thing,

55
00:03:58,428 --> 00:04:00,508
and that’s being arranged.

56
00:04:00,508 --> 00:04:03,978
If it’s out of a genuine 
service necessity,

57
00:04:03,978 --> 00:04:08,748
the paraphernalia for sevā
will come to that person.

58
00:04:08,748 --> 00:04:10,924
That’s a guarantee.

59
00:04:10,924 --> 00:04:14,702
When Śrīla Saraswatī Ṭhākur
was wondering about

60
00:04:14,702 --> 00:04:17,222
getting the inspiration
to start Gaudiya Math,

61
00:04:17,222 --> 00:04:20,192
and all those activities 
that would ensue,

62
00:04:20,192 --> 00:04:23,292
and wondering,
“Where will the funding come?”

63
00:04:23,292 --> 00:04:27,762
Then, we’re told,

64
00:04:27,762 --> 00:04:30,762
that he had a vision 
of the Pañcha Tattva.

65
00:04:30,762 --> 00:04:35,858
And they’re reassuring him 
not to worry about these things—

66
00:04:35,858 --> 00:04:43,356
that all the resources necessary
for sevā will be supplied.

67
00:04:43,356 --> 00:04:47,270
That faith we must have.

68
00:04:47,270 --> 00:04:52,620
But for it to be real and substantial 
it has to be sevā.

69
00:04:52,620 --> 00:04:58,230
Actually sevā … That means for Kṛṣṇa’s
enjoyment satisfaction.

